# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#  Operon Intelligence — Environment Variables Reference
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
#  This file documents ALL environment variables used across the project.
#  DO NOT copy this file — use the per-service .env.example files instead:
#
#    frontend/.env.example   →  copy to  frontend/.env
#    backend/.env.example    →  copy to  backend/.env
#
# ─── FRONTEND (frontend/.env) ───────────────────────────────────────────────
#
#  VITE_DEEPSEEK_API_KEY
#    Used by: src/services/deepseek.ts
#    Purpose: Generates 50 new synthetic complaints every 10 minutes to keep
#             the demo pool fresh when the live CFPB API is unavailable.
#    Optional: Yes — without it, the 600-complaint seed pool is static.
#    Provider: https://platform.deepseek.com
#
#  VITE_DEEPSEEK_API_KEY=your_key_here
#
# ─── BACKEND (backend/.env) ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
#  OPENAI_API_KEY
#    Used by: backend/agents/orchestrator.py (and all agent files)
#    Purpose: Powers the 5-agent LangGraph pipeline:
#             Classification → Compliance Risk → Routing → Resolution → QA
#    Optional: Yes — without it, the Agent views return errors, but all
#             CFPB data views (Dashboard, LiveFeed, Analysis, etc.) work fine.
#    Provider: https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
#
#  OPENAI_API_KEY=your_key_here
#
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
